content: App(s) work fairly well except for watch builder. Installed on my Vivoactive 3, and even though I've paid and unlocked the program, it continues to be deactivated from my watch.
replyContent: Hi Rob. Thanks for your review. Which watch builder are you using? Is it the "Watch Face Builder" or the "Watchmaker"? If it's the first option, you need to generate the unlock code fo the user ID, and paste it into the settings. If it's the second option, you must generate the layout using the premium r.485 app (not the free one). Best regards

content: Fantastic, really for the developers efforts I don't know what other people's issues are but my device is a Garmin vivo active 3 music. I installed the maps and create my route. I then save the route and then load it to my device which then loads the maps and whatnot. Great work!

Very disappointed, every time i open this app is staying in demo mode until you synchronise to your garmin watch (fenix 5). The actual MAP (THE ONLY REASON I PURCHASED) disappeared after little while every time. Do not recommend to buy this app

The only 3rd party apps I run on my vivoactive 3. For me, the amount of useful app's and tools you get easily justify the cost. Sure the UI isn't may not be the cleanest, and maybe not the most intuitive but the dev has excellent guides as well as video's, and once you figure it out it's pretty straight forward and just works and works great. Best part is, the developer is amazing in regards to responding quickly to support requests. That to me is huge.

Nonintuitive and clunky. I eventually got a map and a route up on my Venu, however it was with great difficulty. To add insult to injury the watch app stayed at my home location for the entire run route. The mega pack is also full of random apps which seemingly have no purpose? After you purchase the app you also still have the 'demo' displays which is just irritating.
6x not exist in menu

Been looking for a good data field display. DBF is awesome...love that I can make the fields I really need to see larger...also helps that I don't wear my glasses when I run. Great customer service...got a response within 2 hrs of contacting them!

A lot of cash for a lot of JUNK, was hoping for a decent data field editor which isnt even remotely workin nor does is know my 2019 watch... but if you need 20 different map designs for driving your bus trough your calendar this is the app for you!!! ofc some of the individual r.485 apps still want a donation key even if you have this majestic pack... so stay away ;)

Freezes vivoactive 3 on removal of widgets.
replyContent: Hi Pete. Thanks for your review. There's indeed a problem with uninstalling, which is absolutely not our fault. This is managed by Garmin software and is affecting apps from other third-party developers. Please check their website: https://forums.garmin.com/forum/developers/connect-iq/1441534-uninstall-issues-with-apps-not-just-watch-faces
